cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on machine translation for African languages using neural machine translation techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also makes use of artificial intelligence techniques, such as neural networks, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The use of neural networks also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category. Additionally, the paper deals with low-resource languages, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well as cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing.
